Reasoning: The paper focuses on anomaly detection in high-dimensional image space using an unsupervised approach with a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a common technique in the sub-category of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of an encoder-decoder architecture, which is a common technique in the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a reconstruction error metric, which is a common technique in the sub-category of Neural Networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed approach to X-ray security screening, which falls under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
